casebody.data:
SARA WOLFE, TRADING AS WOLFE’S LOAN OFFICE, PLAINTIFF-APPELLANT, v. THE MAYOR AND ALDERMEN OF JERSEY CITY AND LUKE BURKE, PROPERTY CLERK OF JERSEY CITY, DEFENDANTS-RESPONDENTS. Decided March 14, 1925.

Before Justices Teen chard, Minturh and Lloyd.

For the petitioner, Herman Lipschitz. Contra, Thomas J. Brogan. Per Curiam.

The above-mentioned petition having been read and considered the same is hereby denied.
